I had the privilege of working with some of my favorite dancers and crew yesterday!! Felt so good to be back on set. 🎥 
• Shout out to @jacob.hiss for bringing my vision to another level, your talents are unmatched.
• To my assistances @megananna_g @zoe.edan @pabliee y’all never fail to hold down the fort and I wouldn’t be the artist I am today without your support and friendship. 
• And to my dancers… I’m speechless!!!! We pieced this together again (for some of you just one reh) and brought It back to life and better than I could have ever imagined. You all are truly genius storytellers. I can’t wait to connect to the world with our story, “Glimpse Of Us”, a story that so many people can relate to, a story that holds a really special place in my heart, and a story I will never forget you all telling on this day. Thank you forever.
• last but not least, to @sushitrash, Thank you for your music bc this song gave me a space to heal.

Been exploring this one for a bit, did my first go in January and here we are. I love that dance can feel so timeless, It changes and grows for me daily, but old combos intention never die, sometimes It changes sometimes I doesn’t. I always remember where they come from, and it keeps me grateful for the pain I feel because I know it makes me stronger. For this one, I’m still sitting in the original intention, which isn’t a great feeling.. but I’m creating a full piece to It for the next Choreographers Carnival and I’m really excited to heal through this creation and just let It all go. Thanks to all the dancers exploring this one with me. Lmk if you need the class video link! Can’t wait to post the rest.

OH I LUV IT & I H8T IT @ THE SAME TIME 🎶 choreo by @cat_cogliandro ✨ #reunited
•
It’s been a long long time since Cat and I got to vibe in the studio together, It was a special day.  A lot of fond memories flood back in me throughout the day (@destyneecanaris i miss you). It’s funny how time can separate people, and bring them back, and do It again. This is how most of my closest friendships are since I’m constantly traveling and moving. It gets lonely sometimes living in big cities. But this, this day really reminded me so so much about my community, my family, my people who have done nothing but lift me up time and time again no matter how much space life puts between us. And I’m glad for this reminder. We laughed, created, vibed, It was marvelous. Mostly I dance to forget, but this night I got to dance to remember. And It felt really good. Thank you cat cat for everything always @cat_cogliandro
No more 🥀

What is Gina’s class?
Gina’s contemporary fusion/improv teaching sessions offer a judgement free zone focusing to build and explore personal confidence with movement expression. She incorporates sense memory as a tool for dancers to discover their genuine, emotional reaction to the music and moves to create an authentic performance quality and confidence that lights up a room. Her mission is to guide dancers through physical and mental training, to unlock the body's full spectrum of movement and expression.

Turn into yourself again and reach on out to become your true self. ✨You know me well✨ @sharonvanhalen

Cat Cogliandro (they/them) is an accomplished dancer with a BFA from SUNY Purchase and an MFA from the University of Arizona. They've collaborated with renowned creators like Cherice Barton, Phillip Chbeeb, Tyce Diorio, Ian Eastwood, and more, earning recognition in The New York Times, Dance Spirit Magazine, and other publications. Cat currently teaches at Joffrey Ballet School, Broadway Dance Center, and Steps on Broadway. They're a global educator and choreographer, leading workshops and participating in dance camps worldwide. Additionally, Cat directs The Dance Safe, an organization advocating for abuse survivors in the dance community and promoting safe and inclusive environments. 🩰 🌎

“The Prelude” (an excerpt modified for YCF)

This is a prelude (and work in progress) to something I started developing in grad school. Something so real, so close. As I type this…it feels more relevant than ever. It’s…The DownFall (of humanity via the lens of social media) and I think it speaks for itself.

I’m grateful for the privilege and luck I have to create art and share it. To dive into it with people who want to change the world. To access it as a space to heal. To access it as platform to create change. I hope for that always.

Thanks @ginamenichino and all who have brought this story to life. I can’t wait to keep developing it.🚪🐇

Choreography: me + in collaboration with @ginamenichino (who learned this on zoom! Sister, you will always be one of my favorite people to work with. I love you.)
Lead artist: @ginamenichino
Supporting artists: @melindamatticoli @yardensharon1 @partisth @steph_lacy
Music: @patrickwatsonofficial
